Department: Computer Science
Subject Name: Operating System Concepts


1. What are the three main purposes of an operating system.
A. manage the computer's resources
B. establish a user interface
C. execute and provide services for applications software
D. All of above	
ANSWER: D 

2. Which of the following are the disadvantages of multiprocessor systems.
A. memory and CPUs are accessed simultaneously
B. multiple processes can be executed simultaneously
C. complicated to schedule processes and allocate the resources to processes
D. Both A and B
ANSWER: D

3. How you define system call in OS?
A. It is another name of memory 
B. It is an interface for a user to use the functions provided by OS
C. It is the error when we access an array out of boundary
D. Both A and B
ANSWER: B

4. What is difference between protection and security in OS
A. Security concerns with the threats and issues attacking within a system while protections resolves the issues coming from outside the system
B. Security concerns with the threats and issues attacking outside a system while protections resolves the issues within the system
C. Security deals with the memory access and protection deals with the hard disk access
D. None of above
ANSWER: A 

5. Which of the following activities relate to process management in OS. 
A. get device attributes, set device attributes
B. create file, delete file
C. create process, delete process etc.
D. Both B and C 
ANSWER: C

6. Which of the following data is saved in the data section of process. 

A. local variables a d return address
B. global variable
C. current activity of process
D. None of above
Answer: A

7. Which activity changes the state of process from running to ready.

A. trap 
B. interrupt
C. input/output
D. Both A and B
Answer: B 

8. Which of the following component of CPU is connected to RAM. 
A. Registers 
B. Arithmetic Logic Unit (ALU) 
C. Control Unit (CU)
D. None of above
Answer: C 

9. How you define signal in OS.
A. interrupt generated by hardware in a system
B. interrupt generated by software in a system
C. Both A and B
D. it is process creation in Unix OS
Answer: B

10. What is Process Control block in OS. 
A. It saves the status of terminated processes
B. It saves the status of newly created processes
C. It saves the status of processes ready to execute on CPU
D. Both B and C
Answer: C

11. How you define queue header in OS.
A. It saves the pointer to first and last process in ready queue
B. It saves the PCBs of all the processes
C. It saves the status of partially executed processes
D. It saves the status of processes waiting for input/out completion
Answer: B

12. What is the purpose of fork() system call in Unix
A. It creates new device to print a file on printer
B. It creates multiples files to write on disk
C. It opens web browser page to open a webpage
D. It creates a new process
Answer: D

13. What is the purpose of long term scheduler.
A. It selects the process from RAM and allocates CPU
B. It selects the process from hard disk whenever space is empty in RAM
C. It selects the process from printer and allocates CPU
D. Both A and B
Answer: B

14. How you define I/O bound process. 
A. The process that consume maximum time on CPU
B. The process that consume maximum time on I/O
C. The process that consume maximum time on ready queue
D. The process that consume maximum time in hard disk
Answer: B

15. What is advantage of context-switching.
A. It saves a lot of time in process execution
B. The CPU does not do anything while context switch
C. The processes run at ideal speed
D. Multi-tasking is possible with context switching
Answer: D

16. Which of the following statements are FALSE.
A. exec() system call sends a signal to parent process to wait
B. wait() system call overwrite the data of the newly created process
C. Every process is assigned a unique number for identification
D. Both A and B
Answer: D

17. How you define I/O-burst.
A. the time taken by CPU to complete a task
B. the time consumed by process on I/O operations before going to ready state
C. number of CPU clock cycles
D. Both A and B
Answer: B

18. When I/O event occurs, the process switches from _______ to _____ state.
A. Running to waiting
B. Waiting to running
C. Waiting to ready
D. Ready to running
Answer: A

19. Set of all processes waiting for I/O device to be free resides in 
A. Ready queue
B. Job queue
C. Waiting queue
D. I/O queue
Answer: D

20. Short term scheduler is also called as 
A. CPU scheduler
B. Job scheduler
C. Swapper
D. Process scheduler
Answer: A

21. Which of the following statements about parent and child processes is/are FALSE.
A. The child waits until parent terminate
B. Child process is the clone of parent process
C. Parent process will execute faster than child process
D. Both A and C
Answer: D

22. If we run fork() system call for two times in a program, how many processes will create (children processes only).
A. 2 child processes
B. 3 child processes
C. 4 child processes
D. Both A and C
Answer: 3

23. Which system call is used to terminate the process abnormally.
A. exit()
B. abort()
C. wait()
D. Both A and B
Answer: B

24. What is the meaning of preemptive scheduling.
A. when running process is completed without interruption, it is called non-preemptive
B. when running process is interrupted by new process during execution, it is called non-preemptive
C. when waiting process is given priority to make it possible to run in time is called non-preemptive
D. All of above
Answer: B

25. What is the advantage of First Come First Serve (FCFS) Algorithm.
A. Convoy effect
B. Processes are executed in Last in First Out order.
C. Processes having short CPU burst time will be given priority
D. The processes will be executed in the orer in which they arrive the system
Answer: D

FCFS algorithm is non-preemptive. True or False.
A. TRUE
B. FALSE
Answer: A

27. In shortedt job first scheduling, which process is given priority. 
A. the processes having short CPU burst time
B. the processes which comes first in queue
C. the processes having high priority number
D. Both A and C
Answer: A

28. Which of the following is the correct efinition of aging.
A. In FCFS, when the processes wait for long time are given authority to allocate CPU to them selves
B. In SJG, when the processes wait for long time are given authority to allocate CPU to them selves
C. In Priority scheduling, when the processes wait for long time, their priority number is increased so that allocation of CPU to them is possible
D. Both A and C
Answer: C

29. Which scheduling works on time quantumr.
A. FCFS
B. Round Robin
C. SJF
D. Both A and B
Answer: B

30. What is the definition of throughput.
A. Waiting time of a process
B. Total time a process spend in a system
C. Number of processes executed per unit time
D. Maximum utilization of CPU
Answer: C

31. Which scheduling algorithm is also called as FCFS with preemption
A. Round robin
B. Shortest Job First
C. Priority
D. None of above
Answer: A

32. What do you define time quantum.
A. It is the amount of time a process waits for input/output completion
B. It is the time slot given to a process to run on CPU
C. It is the amount of time a process waits for CPU for allocation
D. Both A and C
Answer: B

33. The original source code of the OS is called as
A. system call
B. backbone
C. dark web
D. kernel
Answer: D

34. Singnal is defined as 
A. Hardware interrupt that never ends
B. Software interrupt
C. An infinite loop in a computer program
D. Both B and C
Answer: B

35. Array out of bound access is a type of _____.
A. Interrupt
B. Signal
C. Trap
D. All of above
Answer: B

36. The global data of process is saved in.
A. data section
B. text section
C. program counter
D. None of above
Answer: A

37. Firmware is alos called is also called as
A. Auto executable file
B. Bootstrap loader
C. Graphical User Interface (GUI)
D. None of above
Answer: B

38. How many processes can be in running state at a time in a system.
A. More than one
B. Exactly one
C. Zero
Both B and C
Answer: D

39. Which of the following events can interrupt a running process.
A. interrupt
B. fork a child
C. pressing escap key
C. Both A and B
Answer: D

40. Which of the following are NOT the scheduling criteria.
A. Minimum waiting time
B. Minimum throughput
C. Maximum turnaround time
D. Both B and C
Answer: D

41. What is advantage of SJF.

A. CPU burst time of next process can be determined before time.
B. CPU burst time of next process cannot be determined before time.
C. I/O burst time of all the previous process can be determined before time.
D. Average waiting time of the processes is minimum
Answer: D

41. If two processes have same CPU-Burst time in SJF scheduling, then how the problem will be solved.
A. The process having shorter CPU burst time will go first
B. The process having larger CPU burst time will go first
C. Both A and B
D. The process will be selected at random and allocated CPU
Answer: C

42. What is difference between hard disk and memory.
A. Hard disk refers to temporary data storage and memory refers to permanent data
B. Hard disk refers to permanent data storage and memory refers to temporary data
C. Storage refers to secondary memory devices but memory refers to primary
D. Both B and C
Answer: D

43. Registers are the defined as.
A. A special portion of hard drive is called register
B. Memory area of cache is called register
C. Memory of CPU having limited space and fastest speed
D. None of above
Answer: C

44. In process, stack represents.
A. the program code
B. global variables
C. temporary data, return address etc
D. Both B and C
Answer: C

45. How device queue is maintained in OS.
A. It is the stack of original source code of the processes
B. It contains the queue of process control blocks of processes
C. It contains the list of processes waiting for specific device
D. None of above
Answer: C

46. How many times BSCS will be printed in following code.
fork();
fork();
printf("BSCS\n");
A. 3 times
B. 2 times
C. 5 times
D. 4 times 
Answer: D

47. The child process may have same data as parent process. True Or False.
A. TRUE
B. FALSE
Answer: A

48. Which of the information about a process are stored in PCB.
A. process ID
B. Number of occupied registers
C. position in the ready queue
D. Both A and B
Answer: D

49. What does dispatch do in process state diagram.
A. It changes the process state from running to ready
B. It changes the process state from running to waiting
C. It changes the process state from ready to running
D. All of above
Answer: C

50. The active mode of program is called as 
A. process
B. activity
C. task
D. job
Answer: A
